The paper deals with connectivity augmentation and optimization in planar straight-line graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of Euclidean distance and minimum spanning trees suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves graph theory, specifically the concept of 2-connectivity, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and bounds suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computational optimization (cs.SI).
